---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'April 2026';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Worflo" description="Worflo privacy policy — how we collect, use, and protect your data.">
  <div style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 24px 80px">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--gray-5);font-size:13px;margin-bottom:40px">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--gray-7);line-height:1.8;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:32px">
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">1. What we collect</h2>
        <p>When you connect HubSpot, we store your HubSpot portal ID, portal name, and OAuth access/refresh tokens (encrypted at rest). We collect workflow definitions, version metadata, and execution trace metadata (object IDs, statuses, step timing). We do not store contact PII — only the HubSpot contact or deal IDs referenced in execution logs.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px">We collect your email address when you create an account or invite team members.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">2. How we use it</h2>
        <p>We use your data solely to provide the Worflo service: syncing workflows, storing version history, logging execution traces, and sending alerts you have configured. We do not sell your data or use it for advertising.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">3. Data storage and security</h2>
        <p>Data is stored on AWS infrastructure in Sydney, Australia. OAuth tokens are encrypted at rest using AES-256. All data in transit is encrypted via TLS 1.2+. We perform regular security audits and use automated vulnerability scanning on every deployment.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">4. Data retention</h2>
        <p>Execution traces are retained for 7 days (Free), 90 days (Pro/Agency/Enterprise), or a custom period negotiated with Enterprise customers. Workflow version history is retained for as long as your account is active. On account deletion, all data is permanently removed within 30 days.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">5. Third-party services</h2>
        <p>We use Stripe for billing (subject to Stripe's privacy policy), AWS for hosting, and Anthropic's API for AI diff summaries (only workflow change data — no contact information — is sent). We do not use any advertising trackers or analytics beyond server-side request logs.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">6. Your rights</h2>
        <p>You may request a copy of your data, correction of inaccurate data, or deletion of all data by emailing <a href="mailto:support@worflo.io">support@worflo.io</a>. We will respond within 30 days. You may disconnect HubSpot at any time from the Settings page, which revokes our OAuth access immediately.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">7. Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:support@worflo.io">support@worflo.io</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
